HEADWORD: Transportable
<hw>Trans*port"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>transportable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being
transported.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Incurring, or subject to, the punishment of
transportation; <as>as, a <ex>transportable</ex> offense</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transportal</ent>⟦br⟧
